A camera is an optical instrument that captures images or videos, either as still photographs or moving sequences. It works by focusing light through a lens onto a light-sensitive surface, which could be film or a digital sensor, to record the image. Cameras are used for a wide range of purposes, from personal photography and filmmaking to surveillance and scientific research.

A smartwatch is a portable wearable computer that resembles a wristwatch. Most modern smartwatches are operated via a touchscreen, and rely on mobile apps that run on a connected device (such as a smartphone) in order to provide core functions.
